                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.8576/6–2949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-29T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 29, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 29—9:02 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2547. Re mytel 2539, June 29, 1 p. m. Another telephone conversation with police
                    station indicates that, as result of Foreign Affairs Bureau intercession, matter
                    has been dropped.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 2547, repeated Nanking 1395.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
